<div class="info-background">
    <br>
    <h3>Why The Environment Matters</h3>
    <div class="video-container">
    <iframe 
    src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/B-nEYsyRlYo?si=btlIdddZiUZbU8qA"
    title="YouTube Save the Planet Video" 
    frameborder="0" 
    allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" 
    referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" 
    allowfullscreen>
    </iframe>
</div>
    <p>The environment is the <strong>foundation of all life on Earth</strong>, providing the <strong>air</strong> we breathe, the <strong>water</strong> we drink, and the <strong>food</strong> we eat. 
        It supports <strong>diverse ecosystems</strong> that maintain the planet's delicate balance, ensuring <strong>clean air, fertile soil, and stable weather patterns.</strong> Beyond sustaining life, 
        the environment offers spaces for recreation, inspiration, and cultural significance, enriching our <strong>mental and emotional well-being.</strong> <br><br>However, <strong>human activities</strong> 
        like deforestation, pollution, and climate change are threatening these vital systems. <strong>Protecting the environment is not just about preserving nature; it's about safeguarding our future,</strong> 
        as a healthy environment is essential for economic stability, public health, and the survival of all species, including our own. <br><br>
     <br>
</div>

<br>
<br>

<div class="list"><h2>What Can You Do</h2></div>
<br>
<ul>
    <li><strong>Reduce, Reuse, Recycle: </strong>Minimize waste by reusing items and recycling materials like paper, plastic, and glass.</li>
</ul><br><ul>
    <li><strong>Conserve Water: </strong>Use water-saving devices, fix leaks, and be mindful of water usage in everyday tasks like showering or washing dishes.</li>
</ul><br><ul>
    <li><strong>Use Renewable Energy: </strong>Switch to solar or wind energy to reduce reliance on fossil fuels and lower carbon emissions.</li>
</ul><br><ul>
    <li><strong>Plant Trees: </strong>Trees absorb carbon dioxide, provide oxygen, and help combat deforestation and habitat loss.</li>
</ul><br><ul>
    <li><strong>Support Sustainable Products: </strong>Choose eco-friendly products, like those made from recycled materials or organic farming practices and buy locally made products.</li>
</ul><br><ul>
    <li><strong>Raise Awareness: </strong> Educate yourself and others about environmental issues, share sustainable practices, and advocate for policies that protect natural resources and promote eco-friendly living.</li>
</ul><br>

</main>
<script>
    function toggleDropdown() {
        const dropdown = document.getElementById("dropdownContent");
        dropdown.classList.toggle("show");
    }

    // Close the dropdown if clicking outside of it
    window.onclick = function(event) {
        if (!event.target.matches('.dropbtn')) {
            const dropdowns = document.getElementsByClassName("dropdown-content");
            for (let i = 0; i < dropdowns.length; i++) {
                const openDropdown = dropdowns[i];
                if (openDropdown.classList.contains('show')) {
                    openDropdown.classList.remove('show');
                }
            }
        }
    }
</script>
